6    """ 
7    Diameter protocol implementation for Scapy 
8     
9    This implements the base Diameter protocol RFC6733 and the additional standards:  # noqa: E501 
10       RFC7155, RFC4004, RFC4006, RFC4072, RFC4740, RFC5778, RFC5447, RFC6942, RFC5777  # noqa: E501 
11       ETS29229 V12.3.0 (2014-09), ETS29272 V13.1.0 (2015-03), ETS29329 V12.5.0 (2014-12),  # noqa: E501 
12       ETS29212 V13.1.0 (2015-03), ETS32299 V13.0.0 (2015-03), ETS29210 V6.7.0 (2006-12),  # noqa: E501 
13       ETS29214 V13.1.0 (2015-03), ETS29273 V12.7.0 (2015-03), ETS29173 V12.3.0 (2015-03),  # noqa: E501 
14       ETS29172 V12.5.0 (2015-03), ETS29215 V13.1.0 (2015-03), ETS29209 V6.8.0 (2011-09),  # noqa: E501 
15       ETS29061 V13.0.0 (2015-03), ETS29219 V13.0.0 (2014-12) 
16    
17   IMPORTANT note: 
18       - Some Diameter fields (Unsigned64, Float32, ...) have not been tested yet due to lack  # noqa: E501 
19           of network captures containing AVPs of that types contributions are welcomed.  # noqa: E501 
20   """

50   class I3BytesEnumField (X3BytesField, EnumField):
51       """ 3 bytes enum field """
52   
53       def __init__(self, name, default, enum):
54           EnumField.__init__(self, name, default, enum, "!I")

57   class I3FieldLenField(X3BytesField, FieldLenField):
58       __slots__ = ["length_of", "count_of", "adjust"]
59   
60       def __init__(
61               self,
62               name,
63               default,
64               length_of=None,
65               count_of=None,
66               adjust=lambda pkt,
67               x: x):
68           X3BytesField.__init__(self, name, default)
69           self.length_of = length_of
70           self.count_of = count_of
71           self.adjust = adjust
72   
73       def i2m(self, pkt, x):
74           return FieldLenField.i2m(self, pkt, x)

81   class DRFlags (FlagsField):
82       def i2repr(self, pkt, x):
83           if x is None:
84               return "None"
85           res = hex(int(x))
86           r = ''
87           cmdt = ' Request' if (x & 128) else ' Answer'
88           if x & 15:  # Check if reserved bits are used
89               nb = 8
90               offset = 0
91           else:       # Strip the first 4 bits
92               nb = 4
93               offset = 4
94               x >>= 4
95           for i in range(nb):
96               r += (x & 1) and str(self.names[offset + i][0]) or '-'
97               x >>= 1
98           invert = r[::-1]
99           return res + cmdt + ' (' + invert[:nb] + ')'
100  
101  
102  class DRCode (I3BytesEnumField):
103      def __init__(self, name, default, enum):
104          """enum is a dict of tuples, so conversion is required before calling the actual init method.  # noqa: E501 
105             Note: the conversion is done only once."""
106          enumDict = {}
107          for k, v in enum.items():
108              enumDict[k] = v[0]
109          I3BytesEnumField.__init__(self, name, default, enumDict)
110  
111      def i2repr(self, pkt, x):
112          cmd = self.i2repr_one(pkt, x)
113          sx = str(x)
114          if cmd == sx:
115              cmd = 'Unknown'
116          return sx + " (" + cmd + ")"

123  class AVPFlags (FlagsField):
124      def i2repr(self, pkt, x):
125          if x is None:
126              return "None"
127          res = hex(int(x))
128          r = ''
129          if x & 31:  # Check if reserved bits are used
130              nb = 8
131              offset = 0
132          else:       # Strip the first 5 bits
133              nb = 3
134              offset = 5
135              x >>= 5
136          for i in range(nb):
137              r += (x & 1) and str(self.names[offset + i][0]) or '-'
138              x >>= 1
139          invert = r[::-1]
140          return res + ' (' + invert[:nb] + ')'

143  class AVPVendor (IntField):
144      def i2repr(self, pkt, x):
145          vendor = vendorList.get(x, "Unkown_Vendor")
146          return "%s (%s)" % (vendor, str(x))

253  class Address (StrLenField):
254      def i2repr(self, pkt, x):
255          if x.startswith(b'\x00\x01'):  # IPv4 address
256              return inet_ntoa(x[2:])
257          elif x.startswith(b'\x00\x02'):    # IPv6 address
258              return inet_ntop(socket.AF_INET6, x[2:])
259          else:   # Address format not yet decoded
260              print('Warning: Address format not yet decoded.')
261              return bytes_hex(x)
262  
263      def any2i(self, pkt, x):
264          if x and isinstance(x, str):
265              try:    # Try IPv4 conversion
266                  s = inet_aton(x)
267                  return b'\x00\x01' + s
268              except BaseException:
269                  try:    # Try IPv6 conversion
270                      s = inet_pton(socket.AF_INET6, x)
271                      return b'\x00\x02' + s
272                  except BaseException:
273                      print('Warning: Address format not supported yet.')
274          return b''

307  class ISDN (StrLenField):
308      def i2repr(self, pkt, x):
309          out = b''
310          for char in x:
311              c = orb(char)
312              out += chb(48 + (c & 15))  # convert second digit first
313              v = (c & 240) >> 4
314              if v != 15:
315                  out += chb(48 + v)
316          return out
317  
318      def any2i(self, pkt, x):
319          out = b''
320          if x:
321              fd = True     # waiting for first digit
322              for c in x:
323                  digit = orb(c) - 48
324                  if fd:
325                      val = digit
326                  else:
327                      val = val + 16 * digit
328                      out += chb(val)
329                  fd = not fd
330              if not fd:    # Fill with 'f' if odd number of characters
331                  out += chb(240 + val)
332          return out

343  AVP_Code_length = 4
344  AVP_Flag_length = 1
345  DIAMETER_BYTES_ALIGNMENT = 4
346  AVP_Flags_List = ["x", "x", "x", "x", "x", "P", "M", "V"]
347  
348  
349  def GuessAvpType(p, **kargs):
350      if len(p) > AVP_Code_length + AVP_Flag_length:
351          # Set AVP code and vendor
352          avpCode = struct.unpack("!I", p[:AVP_Code_length])[0]
353          vnd = bool(struct.unpack(
354              "!B", p[AVP_Code_length:AVP_Code_length + AVP_Flag_length])[0] & 128)  # noqa: E501
355          vndCode = struct.unpack("!I", p[8:12])[0] if vnd else 0
356          # Check if vendor and code defined and fetch the corresponding AVP
357          # definition
358          if vndCode in AvpDefDict:
359              AvpVndDict = AvpDefDict[vndCode]
360              if avpCode in AvpVndDict:
361                  # Unpack only the first 4 tuple items at this point
362                  avpName, AVPClass, flags = AvpVndDict[avpCode][:3]
363                  result = AVPClass(p, **kargs)
364                  result.name = 'AVP ' + avpName
365                  return result
366      # Packet too short or AVP vendor or AVP code not found ...
367      return AVP_Unknown(p, **kargs)
368  
369  
370  class AVP_Generic (Packet):
371      """ Parent class for the 5 following AVP intermediate classes below"""
372  
373      def extract_padding(self, s):
374          nbBytes = self.avpLen % DIAMETER_BYTES_ALIGNMENT
375          if nbBytes:
376              nbBytes = DIAMETER_BYTES_ALIGNMENT - nbBytes
377          return s[:nbBytes], s[nbBytes:]
378  
379      def post_build(self, p, pay):
380          nbBytes = (-len(p)) % 4
381          while nbBytes:
382              p += struct.pack("B", 0)
383              nbBytes -= 1
384          return p + pay
385  
386      def show2(self):
387          self.__class__(raw(self), name=self.name).show()
388  
389  
390  def AVP(avpId, **fields):
391      """ Craft an AVP based on its id and optional parameter fields"""
392      val = None
393      classType = AVP_Unknown
394      if isinstance(avpId, str):
395          try:
396              for vnd in AvpDefDict:
397                  for code in AvpDefDict[vnd]:
398                      val = AvpDefDict[vnd][code]
399                      if val[0][:len(
400                              avpId)] == avpId:  # A prefix of the full name is considered valid  # noqa: E501
401                          raise
402              found = False
403          except BaseException:
404              found = True
405      else:
406          if isinstance(avpId, list):
407              code = avpId[0]
408              vnd = avpId[1]
409          else:  # Assume this is an int
410              code = avpId
411              vnd = 0
412          try:
413              val = AvpDefDict[vnd][code]
414              found = True
415          except BaseException:
416              found = False
417      if not found:
418          warning('The AVP identifier %s has not been found.' % str(avpId))
419          if isinstance(avpId, str):  # The string input is not valid
420              return None
421      # At this point code, vnd are provisionned val may be set (if found is True)  # noqa: E501
422      # Set/override AVP code
423      fields['avpCode'] = code
424      # Set vendor if not already defined and relevant
425      if 'avpVnd' not in fields and vnd:
426          fields['avpVnd'] = vnd
427      # Set flags if not already defined and possible ...
428      if 'avpFlags' not in fields:
429          if val:
430              fields['avpFlags'] = val[2]
431          else:
432              fields['avpFlags'] = 128 if vnd else 0
433      # Finally, set the name and class if possible
434      if val:
435          classType = val[1]
436      _ret = classType(**fields)
437      if val:
438          _ret.name = 'AVP ' + val[0]
439      return _ret

485  class AVP_Unknown (AVP_Generic):
486      """ The default structure for AVPs which could not be decoded (optional vendor field, variable length). """  # noqa: E501
487      name = 'AVP Unknown'
488      fields_desc = [
489          IntField("avpCode", None),
490          AVPFlags("avpFlags", None, 8, AVP_Flags_List),
491          I3FieldLenField("avpLen", None, length_of="val",
492                          adjust=lambda pkt, x:x + 8 + ((pkt.avpFlags & 0x80) >> 5)),  # noqa: E501
493          ConditionalField(AVPVendor("avpVnd", 0), lambda pkt:pkt.avpFlags & 0x80),  # noqa: E501
494          StrLenField("val", None,
495                      length_from=lambda pkt:pkt.avpLen - 8 - ((pkt.avpFlags & 0x80) >> 5))  # noqa: E501
496      ]

4708 # Generic class + commands builder

4712 class DiamG (Packet):
4713     """   Generic class defining all the Diameter fields"""
4714     name = "Diameter"
4715     fields_desc = [
4716         # Protocol version field, 1 byte, default value = 1
4717         XByteField("version", 1),
4718         I3FieldLenField(
4719             "drLen",
4720             None,
4721             length_of="avpList",
4722             adjust=lambda p,
4723             x:x +
4724             DR_Header_Length),
4725         DRFlags("drFlags", None, 8, DR_Flags_List),
4726         # Command Code, 3 bytes, no default
4727         DRCode("drCode", None, DR_cmd_def),
4728         # Application ID, 4 bytes, no default
4729         IntEnumField("drAppId", None, AppIDsEnum),
4730         # Hop-by-Hop Identifier, 4 bytes
4731         XIntField("drHbHId", 0),
4732         # End-to-end Identifier, 4 bytes
4733         XIntField("drEtEId", 0),
4734         PacketListField(
4735             "avpList",
4736             [],
4737             GuessAvpType,
4738             length_from=lambda pkt:pkt.drLen -
4739             DR_Header_Length),
4740     ]
4741 
4742 
4743 def getCmdParams(cmd, request, **fields):
4744     """Update or fill the fields parameters depending on command code. Both cmd and drAppId can be provided  # noqa: E501 
4745        in string or int format."""
4746     drCode = None
4747     params = None
4748     drAppId = None
4749     # Fetch the parameters if cmd is found in dict
4750     if isinstance(cmd, int):
4751         drCode = cmd    # Enable to craft commands with non standard code
4752         if cmd in DR_cmd_def:
4753             params = DR_cmd_def[drCode]
4754         else:
4755             params = ('Unknown', 'UK', {0: (128, 0)})
4756             warning(
4757                 'No Diameter command with code %d found in DR_cmd_def dictionary' %  # noqa: E501
4758                 cmd)
4759     else:  # Assume command is a string
4760         if len(cmd) > 3:     # Assume full command name given
4761             fpos = 0
4762         else:         # Assume abbreviated name is given and take only the first two letters  # noqa: E501
4763             cmd = cmd[:2]
4764             fpos = 1
4765         for k, f in DR_cmd_def.items():
4766             if f[fpos][:len(
4767                     cmd)] == cmd:   # Accept only a prefix of the full name
4768                 drCode = k
4769                 params = f
4770                 break
4771         if not drCode:
4772             warning(
4773                 'Diameter command with name %s not found in DR_cmd_def dictionary.' %  # noqa: E501
4774                 cmd)
4775             return (fields, 'Unknown')
4776     # The drCode is set/overridden in any case
4777     fields['drCode'] = drCode
4778     # Processing of drAppId
4779     if 'drAppId' in fields:
4780         val = fields['drAppId']
4781         if isinstance(val, str):   # Translate into application Id code
4782             found = False
4783             for k, v in AppIDsEnum.items():
4784                 if v.find(val) != -1:
4785                     drAppId = k
4786                     fields['drAppId'] = drAppId
4787                     found = True
4788                     break
4789             if not found:
4790                 del fields['drAppId']
4791                 warning(
4792                     'Application ID with name %s not found in AppIDsEnum dictionary.' %  # noqa: E501
4793                     val)
4794                 return (fields, 'Unknown')
4795         else:   # Assume type is int
4796             drAppId = val
4797     else:  # Application Id shall be taken from the params found based on cmd
4798         drAppId = next(iter(params[2]))   # The first record is taken
4799         fields['drAppId'] = drAppId
4800     # Set the command name
4801     name = params[0] + '-Request' if request else params[0] + '-Answer'
4802     # Processing of flags (only if not provided manually)
4803     if 'drFlags' not in fields:
4804         if drAppId in params[2]:
4805             flags = params[2][drAppId]
4806             fields['drFlags'] = flags[0] if request else flags[1]
4807     return (fields, name)
4808 
4809 
4810 def DiamReq(cmd, **fields):
4811     """Craft Diameter request commands"""
4812     upfields, name = getCmdParams(cmd, True, **fields)
4813     p = DiamG(**upfields)
4814     p.name = name
4815     return p
4816 
4817 
4818 def DiamAns(cmd, **fields):
4819     """Craft Diameter answer commands"""
4820     upfields, name = getCmdParams(cmd, False, **fields)
4821     p = DiamG(**upfields)
4822     p.name = name
4823     return p
